feat(vuln): Stage 3 - Tier-1 passive vulnerability scanners with authorization gate

Plan: argus-three-gap-closure-623653.md, Stage 3.

Adds 4 lightweight passive vuln scanners gated by an explicit
authorization check. Argus is now able to discover real vulnerabilities
on authorized targets (DVWA SQLi, AltoroJ XSS) instead of stopping at
recon-only output.

=== utils/authorization.py ===
is_authorized_target(url) -> (allowed: bool, reason: str)

Two-path gate (either passes):
  1. host hits config.toml [security] allowed_domains
  2. host hits ~/.argus/credentials.toml [targets.*]
     (holding credentials = proven authorization)

When neither path matches, returns a clear remediation message
listing both ways to grant authorization. This is the FINAL guard;
engine-level whitelist is left in place but not relied on for
parameter shapes specific to each vuln tool.

=== tools/vuln_scan.py ===

vuln_sqli_timing(url, param, method='GET', baseline_samples=3)
  Time-blind SQL injection probe.
  - Establish baseline median latency (3 samples by default)
  - Try 4 SLEEP/WAITFOR payloads (MySQL, PostgreSQL, MSSQL flavors)
  - Trigger condition: payload_latency - baseline >= 2.0s and < 8.0s
    (lower bound: SLEEP took effect; upper: not network jitter/timeout)
  - Confidence: high (>=3 triggers), medium (2), low (1), none (0)

vuln_xss_reflection(url, param, method='GET')
  XSS reflection probe with HTML-encoding awareness.
  - Inject random token: <argus_xss_probe_<rand6>>
  - Detect both raw reflection AND HTML-encoded reflection
  - vulnerable = raw_reflected AND NOT encoded
    (encoded reflection means server is sanitizing - safe)
  - Captures 60-char context around the hit for triage

vuln_open_redirect(url, redirect_param)
  External-domain Location header probe.
  - 3 payload variants: //evil, https://evil, /\evil
  - follow_redirects=False to inspect raw Location
  - Hit: 3xx status + Location contains probe domain

vuln_cors_misconfig(url)
  Arbitrary-Origin echo probe.
  - Origin: https://argus-cors-probe.example
  - Severity tiers:
      high   = arbitrary Origin echoed AND Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true
      medium = arbitrary Origin echoed (no credentials)
      low    = ACAO: * (wildcard, evaluate API sensitivity)
      none   = no CORS misconfig

All 4 tools:
  - check is_authorized_target FIRST; refuse and return clear reason if not
  - return JSON-formatted summary string for LLM consumption
  - timeout=15s, verify=False, custom UA "Mozilla/5.0 (Argus-VulnScan)"

=== Engine integration (agent/engine.py) ===
TOOL_RISK_LEVELS: 4 vuln_* tools all -> 'block'
BLOCK_RISK_HINTS: 4 hints emphasizing 'authorized pen test only',
                  warns that target IDS/WAF will log the activity

=== Tests (+17, all green) ===
test_vuln_scan.py:
  - authorization gate: unauthorized blocked, authorized proceeds
  - sqli: baseline-only no signal, sleep detected (mock _measure
    avoids real-time delays)
  - xss: unencoded reflection vulnerable, encoded reflection safe,
    no-echo safe
  - open_redirect: external Location vulnerable, same-origin safe
  - cors: arbitrary+credentials high, wildcard low, no-acao none
  - all 4 tools registered, all 4 risk-level=block, all 4 in hints
  - authorization paths: allowed_domains, credentials.toml,
    unauthorized produces clear remediation message

=== Cumulative ===
Tests 721 -> 738 (+17). Tools 48 -> 52 (+4). ruff/mypy clean
(64 source files).

